    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_kard" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kard</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>нож</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>knife</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сабля</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sabre</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(в
                            эпосе)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in the
                            epics)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>меч</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(в эпосе)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">(in the epics)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sword</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>xsargard</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>шашка</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>cavalry sword</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>kærdʒæm</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>ножны</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>sheath</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>xæskard</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>ножницы</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>scissors</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>jæ kard æm radta G˳ymag læg Sozyryqomæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Гумский человек дал свой нож Созруко</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>The man of Gum gave his knife to Sozruko</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>sæ kard ū syǧdæg saw qanʒal</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сабля у них — настоящий черный %sкандзал%s (из высокосортной
                                стали)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>their sabre is a real black %skandzal%s (made of high-quality
                                steel)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>500</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Batraz kard islasta ma wæjugæn æ sær rakʼwærdta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Батраз извлек меч и снес у великана голову</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Batraz drew his sword out and cut the giant's head off</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>437</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xastoj bazarmæ wæjmæ alyǧ˳yzon kærdtæ, qamatæ, toppytæ,
                            dambacatæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>несли на базар для продажи всевозможные сабли, кинжалы, ружья,
                                пистолеты</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(some people) carried to the bazaar for sale all sorts of sabers,
                                daggers, guns, pistols</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>72</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Иранское слово, усвоенное во многие другие языки: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kārd</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kārt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kērd, kēr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>kārč</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>čāra</w></mentioned> (← %i*kartyā%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>)
                    ‘нож’, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čēd</w>
                        <gloss><q>нож</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>kir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>kēl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kēra</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>149</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>kero</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>köz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kart</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kart(krt-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kar-əta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>нож</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        dialect="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w>krti-</w>
                        <gloss><q>нож</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        dialect="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>кинжал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kartari-</w>
                        <gloss><q>охотничий нож</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>kerte</w>
                        <gloss><q>меч</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Arch._Or."/><biblScope>XVIII 129</biblScope></bibl>). С
                    давних пор свидетельствуется на славянской и угро-финской почве, куда оно вошло
                    из иранского: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>коръда</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>кордъ</w>
                        <gloss><q>род меча</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Срезневский"/><biblScope>I 1285</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cs"><lang/>
                        <w>kord</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pl"><lang/>
                        <w>kord</w>
                        <gloss><q>шпага</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>569</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>kard</w>
                        <gloss><q>меч</q></gloss></mentioned> (вероятно, из аланского), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kca" dialect="kca"><lang/>
                        <w>karta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mns" dialect="mns"><lang/>
                        <w>kort</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>kört</w>
                        <gloss><q>железо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="chm"><lang/>
                        <w>kerdo</w>
                        <gloss><q>сабля</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>dukardi</w>
                        <gloss><q>ножницы для стрижки овец</q></gloss></mentioned> (← <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dō-kārd</w></mentioned>). — Иранское слово заключает общеиндоевропейскую
                    глагольную основу %i*k˳ert-%i ‘резать’, иран. %ikart-%i, которая наличествует в
                    ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdyn"/> | %ikærdum%i. Ср. также <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_kærdæn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gærdyn"/>,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"/> | %iævgærdun%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ævgærdæn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xsargard"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_kærdʒæm"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæskard"
                            />.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                            50, 78</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Munkácsi._Alan."/><biblScope>IV
                            380</biblScope></bibl>%b!!Munkácsi. KSz. IV 380!!%b. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl>.
                    — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 171,
                            251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">An Iranian word, which entered many other languages: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kārd</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kārt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>kērd, kēr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>kārč</w></mentioned>,<mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>čāra</w></mentioned> (← %i*kartyā%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>)
                    ‘knife’, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>čēd</w>
                        <gloss><q>khife</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>kir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>kēl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kēra</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>149</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>kero</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>köz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>kart</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kart(krt-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kar-əta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>нож</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(вед.) </note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">(Vedic) </note><w>krti-</w>
                        <gloss><q>knife</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>dagger</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kartari-</w>
                        <gloss><q>hunting knife</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>kerte</w>
                        <gloss><q>sword</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Arch._Or."/><biblScope>XVIII 129</biblScope></bibl>). It
                    has long been attested in the Slavic and Ugro-Finnic context, where it was
                    acquired from Iranian: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>коръда</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="orv"><lang/>
                        <w>кордъ</w>
                        <gloss><q>the type of sword</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Срезневский"/><biblScope>I 1285</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="cs"><lang/>
                        <w>kord</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pl"><lang/>
                        <w>kord</w>
                        <gloss><q>rapier</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>569</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
                        <w>kard</w>
                        <gloss><q>sword</q></gloss></mentioned> (probably, from Alanian), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kca" dialect="kca"><lang/>
                        <w>karta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mns" dialect="mns"><lang/>
                        <w>kort</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>kört</w>
                        <gloss><q>iron</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="chm"><lang/>
                        <w>kerdo</w>
                        <gloss><q>sabre</q></gloss></mentioned>. See also <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>dukardi</w>
                        <gloss><q>sheep shears</q></gloss></mentioned> (← <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dō-kārd</w></mentioned>). — The Iranian word contains a common
                    Indo-European verb stem %i*k˳ert-%i ‘to cut’, Iranian %ikart-%i, which is
                    present in Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdyn"/> | %ikærdum%i. See
                    also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdæn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_gærdyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærgævdyn"/> |
                    %iævgærdun%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævgærdæn"/>, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xsargard"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdʒæm"/>, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_xæskard"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 78</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Munkácsi.
                            </author><biblScope>KSz. IV 380</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl>.
                    — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 171,
                            251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
